We’ll outline several implications:

A) their tragic frame operates as a total solvency takeout to the affirmative—their aff is premised on productively sublimating affects through confrontations with trauma—but they don’t meet their own standard—for a tragedian only an epochal and apolcayptic confrontation with the root of trauma can solve—by only addressing one specific instance of hyperarousal they fail to clear their own bar for encountering the root cause of trauma rather than a single proximate cause

B) Magnifies all alternate causality arguments into solvency turns rather than solvency takeouts—any alternate causality for hyperarousal is framed by the aff as a fundamentally tragic encounter with a fixed truth of political reality—this means the return of hyperarousal is not taken as a temporary attitudinal or political mistake but instead as an absolute enunciation of the death drive

C) Tragic framing results in scapegoating and mass violence- comic framing solves by sublimating the system as weak and sensiting the people to its fragility
Carlson, Assist. Comm Prof @ Maryland, 1986 p. EBSCO (Cheree, in Quarterly Journal of Speech “Ghandi and the Comic Frame”)
